external_knowledge:
- A 'top' player refers to the one with the highest average performance value within their team; 
- 'Soccer' is a team sport played between two teams of eleven players using a round ball with the objective of scoring more goals than the opposing team by kicking or heading the ball into the opponent's goal; 
- Average performance is a quantitative measure of an athlete's skills and abilities.

sql:
SELECT MAX(improvement_value) AS max_improvement
FROM improvements
WHERE athlete_id = 1;

SELECT name 
FROM athletes 
ORDER BY name;

external_knowledge:
- Significant improvement and top performances refer to the top three highest performance and improvement values for each athlete, which are ranked based on the performance_value and improvement_value, respectively; 
- Average performance refers to the mean of the top three performance values for each athlete; 
- Top 10 results refer to the athletes with the highest average performance values, up to a maximum of 10 athletes.
